{
  "sectionCode": "331",
  "sectionCodeDisplay": "331",
  "title": "The Cellular Basis of Form and Function",
  "outline": [
    {
      "level": "A",
      "levelType": "major",
      "text": "Cell theory and classification",
      "children": [
        {
          "level": "1",
          "levelType": "numeric",
          "text": "The cell theory",
          "children": [
            {
              "level": "a",
              "levelType": "lowercase",
              "text": "Historical background",
              "children": []
            },
            {
              "level": "b",
              "levelType": "lowercase",
              "text": "Challenges to and revisions of the cell theory in the light of later knowledge",
              "children": []
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "level": "2",
          "levelType": "numeric",
          "text": "Classification of cells",
          "children": [
            {
              "level": "a",
              "levelType": "lowercase",
              "text": "General features: comparisons between cells and viruses and between procaryotic and eucaryotic cells, tissues as providing a functional classification of cells",
              "children": []
            },
            {
              "level": "b",
              "levelType": "lowercase",
              "text": "Cells and tissues of animals: absorptive cells, secretory cells, nerve cells, sensory cells, muscle cells, cells in supporting tissues, circulating cells, reproductive cells",
              "children": []
            },
            {
              "level": "c",
              "levelType": "lowercase",
              "text": "Cells and tissues of higher plants: outstanding features of the plant cell; meristematic, epidermal, and other types of plant cells",
              "children": []
            },
            {
              "level": "d",
              "levelType": "lowercase",
              "text": "Comparison between animal cells and plant cells",
              "children": []
            }
          ]
        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "level": "B",
      "levelType": "major",
      "text": "Cell design and cell organization",
      "children": [
        {
          "level": "1",
          "levelType": "numeric",
          "text": "The cell as a molecular system",
          "children": [
            {
              "level": "a",
              "levelType": "lowercase",
              "text": "Macromolecules in cells: nucleic acids, proteins, polysaccharides",
              "children": []
            },
            {
              "level": "b",
              "levelType": "lowercase",
              "text": "Small molecules in cells: lipids, nucleotides, amino acids, fatty acids",
              "children": []
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "level": "2",
          "levelType": "numeric",
          "text": "Form and structure of the cell",
          "children": [
            {
              "level": "a",
              "levelType": "lowercase",
              "text": "Sizes and shapes of cells",
              "children": []
            },
            {
              "level": "b",
              "levelType": "lowercase",
              "text": "Morphological elements: parts of cells--cell membrane, extracellular matrix, mitochondria, ribosomes, cytoskeleton, nuclear envelope, chromosomes, nucleolus",
              "children": []
            },
            {
              "level": "c",
              "levelType": "lowercase",
              "text": "Procaryotic and eucaryotic cells [see also 312.A.3.b.]",
              "children": []
            }
          ]
        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "level": "C",
      "levelType": "major",
      "text": "Functional aspects of cells",
      "children": [
        {
          "level": "1",
          "levelType": "numeric",
          "text": "The internal environment and the cell matrix: the concept of the cell as a \"protoplasm,\" the concept of the cell as a \"bag\" containing a water solution of molecules",
          "children": []
        },
        {
          "level": "2",
          "levelType": "numeric",
          "text": "Cell membranes [see 323.A.]",
          "children": []
        },
        {
          "level": "3",
          "levelType": "numeric",
          "text": "Interplay of nucleus and cytoplasm",
          "children": []
        },
        {
          "level": "4",
          "levelType": "numeric",
          "text": "Cell movement: ciliary, flagellar, and amoeboid",
          "children": []
        },
        {
          "level": "5",
          "levelType": "numeric",
          "text": "Cells in combination: cohesion and communication to form tissues and multicellular organisms",
          "children": []
        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "level": "D",
      "levelType": "major",
      "text": "The cell cycle",
      "children": [
        {
          "level": "1",
          "levelType": "numeric",
          "text": "Cell growth: doubling of size, genetic replication, preparation for division",
          "children": []
        },
        {
          "level": "2",
          "levelType": "numeric",
          "text": "Cell division",
          "children": [
            {
              "level": "a",
              "levelType": "lowercase",
              "text": "Mitosis: condensation of chromosomes and dissolution of nuclear envelope; splitting of chromosomes; formation of new nuclear envelopes",
              "children": []
            },
            {
              "level": "b",
              "levelType": "lowercase",
              "text": "Cytokinesis: constriction of animal cell into halves by contractile ring of actin filaments, division of plant cell by formation of cell plate and new cell wall",
              "children": []
            },
            {
              "level": "c",
              "levelType": "lowercase",
              "text": "Meiosis: division of germ cell into gametes, or reproductive cells, each with one-half of the genetic material of parent cell",
              "children": []
            }
          ]
        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "level": "E",
      "levelType": "major",
      "text": "Fertilization",
      "children": [
        {
          "level": "1",
          "levelType": "numeric",
          "text": "Characteristics of the mature egg",
          "children": []
        },
        {
          "level": "2",
          "levelType": "numeric",
          "text": "Events of fertilization",
          "children": []
        },
        {
          "level": "3",
          "levelType": "numeric",
          "text": "Biochemical analysis of the events of fertilization",
          "children": []
        }
      ]
    }
  ],
